    <h2>PAGe</h2>
    <p>
The Pneumococcal African Genome project (PAGe) is a consortium funded by the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation 
focused on genomic analysis of the pneumococcus across Africa. Its goals include:

  
        <ol style="margin-left: 1em;">
            <li>Capacity building in bioinformatics and molecular epidemiology</li>
            <li>Understanding the epidemiology of specific pneumococcal serotypes</li>
            <li>Identifying new opportunities for disease control with current vaccines </li>
            <li>Delivering knowledge to create the next generation of pneumococcal vaccines</li>
        </ol>
   
